data.name: Label5.Text
data.value:
Select you password.
The password will be used to encrypt and decrypt the lock file, to give you access to Raptor interface and unlock the PC if you don't have the USB key handy. Password must be at least 6 characters long.

data.name: Label8.Text
data.value:
Select lock type
Raptor lock will lock your PC right after the USB is removed and will unlock it when the key is inserted again in one of the computer USB ports. The most of the program functions are available only under this selection. Windows lock will lock the PC using the standard widnows method. The automatic unlock is not available when you select this kind of lock and you will be forced to enter your windows password to unlock your system.

data.name: Label10.Text
data.value: It seems that the file is not present to your system! Please check your USB drive status and try again by clicking the "Create file" button. If you procced to next step without retrying you will not be able to enable Raptor.

data.name: Label11.Text
data.value: Now you can enable the program and start using it. Please notice that the program in order to protect you from accidental system locks it needs to detect the encryption key before it goes in arm state. For more info about this you have to read the program documentation.

data.name: Label1.Text
data.value:
Welcome to USB Raptor. USB Raptor is a utility which can help you secure your PC by using a USB flash drive as unlock key. The utilty scans the USB removable drives to find a unique encrypted key. This key is decrypted and compared with program's settings, if the decryption result matches program's settings the PC stays unlocked, otherwise PC is locked. There are two different types of locks available: Windows lock and Raptor lock.
This wizard will guide you through the basic steps to configure the utility. It is important to follow the steps provided. This wizard runs only one time on each PC.
